# Always Read Development Log

## Rule
ALWAYS read and reference the `development-log.md` file at the start of any AI session to understand the current project context, previous decisions, and what has been accomplished.

## Requirements
- Read the entire development log before making any suggestions or starting work
- Pay special attention to the Quick Notes section for user preferences and guidelines
- Reference previous AI decisions and context when relevant
- Understand the current project phase and what has been completed
- Build upon previous work rather than starting from scratch
- Maintain continuity between different AI sessions

## Purpose
This prevents re-explaining context and maintains continuity between AI interactions. The development log contains:
- Current project context and phase
- Quick Notes section with user preferences and important guidelines
- Previous AI decisions and reasoning
- Files that have been changed
- Important context for future sessions

## Implementation
- Start every session by reading `development-log.md`
- Reference relevant previous entries when making decisions
- Add new entries to the log after significant work
- Keep the log updated with latest context
